Excitement is building as the city gears up for the annual sardine run. DURBAN - Something fishy is headed for Durban. Excitement is building as the city gears up for the annual sardine run. Experts are predicting large shoals will move past the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast, soon. Shoals of sardines have already been spotted in Waterfall Bluff in Port St Johns, south of KwaZulu-Natal’s coastline. READ: Durban beaches temporarily closed for sardine run Last year’s run was nothing short of spectacular. The public can freely watch the spectacle. Permits are needed for anglers and those casting nets.